{"title":"Deprecating cssnext","headings":[{"level":2,"text":"tl;dr","id":"tldr"},{"level":2,"text":"Why are you doing this?","id":"why-are-you-doing-this"},{"level":2,"text":"Why didn't you give the project to someone else?","id":"why-didnt-you-give-the-project-to-someone-else"},{"level":2,"text":"Why don't you just let this thing rot?","id":"why-dont-you-just-let-this-thing-rot"},{"level":2,"text":"Migration to postcss-preset-env","id":"migration-to-postcss-preset-env"},{"level":3,"text":"Removed","id":"removed"},{"level":3,"text":"Added","id":"added"},{"level":4,"text":"Available but inactive by default (Stage 3+ is active by default):","id":"available-but-inactive-by-default-stage-3-is-active-by-default"}],"date":"2018-05-29T00:00:00.000Z","tags":["css"],"body":{"tag":"div","children":[{"tag":"p","children":["Following my ",{"tag":"a","props":{"href":"/blog/farewell-css/"},"children":["farewell to CSS"]},", I am deprecating\n",{"tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://cssnext.github.io"},"children":["cssnext"]},"."]},"\n",{"tag":"h2","props":{"id":"tldr"},"children":[{"tag":"a","props":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#tldr"},"children":[{"tag":"span","props":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"tl;dr"]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Just switch to ",{"tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://preset-env.cssdb.org/"},"children":[{"tag":"code","children":["postcss-preset-env"]}]},"."]},"\n",{"tag":"h2","props":{"id":"why-are-you-doing-this"},"children":[{"tag":"a","props":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#why-are-you-doing-this"},"children":[{"tag":"span","props":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Why are you doing this?"]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Like I said in my ",{"tag":"a","props":{"href":"/blog/farewell-css/"},"children":["farewell to CSS"]}," post, I don't use CSS\ndirectly anymore. And things have been this way for years now. I also have been\ntired of PostCSS (because I disagree with the vision and the directions taken by\nthe project)."]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Beside the fact that I were not using CSS directly anymore, too many PostCSS\nreleases meant that I had to update most of the PostCSS plugins underneath\ncssnext in order to adapt to the new or changed APIs. This was a very time\nconsuming process. At the time being one of the most active PostCSS\ncontributors, I wasn’t always warned about these API changes. This eventually\nmotivated me to just stop contributing to this ecosystem, even if I created the\nPostCSS GitHub organization in the first place."]},"\n",{"tag":"h2","props":{"id":"why-didnt-you-give-the-project-to-someone-else"},"children":[{"tag":"a","props":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#why-didnt-you-give-the-project-to-someone-else"},"children":[{"tag":"span","props":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Why didn't you give the project to someone else?"]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["I tried. I gave 3 of the most active contributors in the cssnext/PostCSS\necosystem rights over the repo, but given everyone’s time and priorities, it\nwasn’t enough to ensure the project would be sufficiently maintained."]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["I also tried to ask for help via Twitter, but no response."]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Then one active member of PostCSS organization made\n",{"tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://preset-env.cssdb.org/"},"children":["a fork (kind of)"]}," and it's probably better\nalready than cssnext ever was. If you still want to use CSS, you should take a\nlook at it."]},"\n",{"tag":"h2","props":{"id":"why-dont-you-just-let-this-thing-rot"},"children":[{"tag":"a","props":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#why-dont-you-just-let-this-thing-rot"},"children":[{"tag":"span","props":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Why don't you just let this thing rot?"]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["That's not my type. I tried to maintain the package for a while, as the number\nof downloads prove that people are actually using it. But now that a solid\nalternative is around (",{"tag":"a","props":{"href":"http://preset-env.cssdb.org/"},"children":[{"tag":"code","children":["postcss-preset-env"]}]},"), I\nthink it's time to deprecate cssnext."]},"\n",{"tag":"h2","props":{"id":"migration-to-postcss-preset-env"},"children":[{"tag":"a","props":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#migration-to-postcss-preset-env"},"children":[{"tag":"span","props":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Migration to ",{"tag":"code","children":["postcss-preset-env"]}]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Migration should be pretty easy."]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["In short, just replace ",{"tag":"code","children":["postcss-cssnext"]}," with ",{"tag":"code","children":["postcss-preset-env"]}," and\n",{"tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/csstools/postcss-preset-env#stage"},"children":["choose your stage"]},"."]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["If you want a sort of changelog, here is what you can expect"]},"\n",{"tag":"h3","props":{"id":"removed"},"children":[{"tag":"a","props":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#removed"},"children":[{"tag":"span","props":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Removed"]},"\n",{"tag":"ul","children":["\n",{"tag":"li","children":["pixrem (generates pixel fallbacks for rem units)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-calc (reduces calc, not really a polyfill)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-color-function (color() is now color-mod())"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-color-rgba-fallback (IE8 fallback for alpha colors)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-pseudoelements (IE8 fallback for : => :: pseudos)"]},"\n"]},"\n",{"tag":"h3","props":{"id":"added"},"children":[{"tag":"a","props":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#added"},"children":[{"tag":"span","props":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Added"]},"\n",{"tag":"ul","children":["\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-color-mod-function (color() is now color-mod())"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-dir-pseudo-class (:dir(ltr) and :dir(rtl) directional selectors)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-focus-visible (requires WICG focus-visible js polyfill)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-focus-within (requires focus-within js polyfill)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-logical (new margin-block, inset, etc. directional properties)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-page-break (fallback break-",{"tag":"em","children":[" properties with page-break-"]}," alias)"]},"\n"]},"\n",{"tag":"h4","props":{"id":"available-but-inactive-by-default-stage-3-is-active-by-default"},"children":[{"tag":"a","props":{"aria-hidden":"true","href":"#available-but-inactive-by-default-stage-3-is-active-by-default"},"children":[{"tag":"span","props":{"class":"icon icon-link"}}]},"Available but inactive by default (Stage 3+ is active by default):"]},"\n",{"tag":"ul","children":["\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-color-rgb (Stage 2)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-custom-media (Stage 2)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-custom-selectors (Stage 2)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-nesting (Stage 1)"]},"\n",{"tag":"li","children":["postcss-apply (Rejected as a standard)"]},"\n"]},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["You will find more accurate and up to date informations on this\n",{"tag":"a","props":{"href":"https://github.com/csstools/postcss-preset-env/issues/32"},"children":["notice to cssnext users on postcss-preset-env repo"]}]},"\n",{"tag":"hr"},"\n",{"tag":"p","children":["Hope this way you don't feel abandonned. This is better for you to upgrade and\nrely on a more mature database, with stages, or like me,\n",{"tag":"a","props":{"href":"/blog/farewell-css/"},"children":["stop using CSS directly"]},"."]}]}}